Format a USB
*************

Execute on the terminal:
lsblk

This will show you the connected disks. 
It will look like this : 

sda      8:0    0 512G  0 disk
├─sda1   8:1    0 500G  0 part
└─sda2   8:2    0  12G  0 part
sdb      8:16   1  16G  0 disk
└─sdb1   8:17   1  16G  0 part

if the usb is mounted you must unmount it

sudo umount /dev/sdb1
(Replace sdb1 with the partition of your usb)



